Author::::Hyz2012
DateTime::::2016-03-11T13:08:50Z
I can't agree enough with what you have said here, speaking as someone who has watched a loved one balance precariously on the edge of destroying themselves with alcoholism for many years. Tough love and making it clear that their behaviour is not acceptable may be the only way to make them look at their own behaviour. Also acknowledging that alcoholism is a disease, that the person is drinking to drown some internal pain that is so bad that only obliterating themselves with drink will help. It's also becoming more clear that the difference between someone who drinks a lot and a true alcoholic is genetic, so even once the person decides to stop, it might be very difficult to do so and a great deal of patience is needed.



