Author::::Skylerwhite1
DateTime::::2016-03-11T12:21:37Z
It sounds very much like your mum is lonely and drinking may help her deal with that. A previous poster mentioned 'breaking the routine' and that's a good place to start. Trips out in the evening, a meal, it doesn't have to be the 'evening class' route, but something she would enjoy, preferably where alcohol isn't the main event. It sounds like she finds solace in drinking and that may numb whatever else she's feeling. It also sounds as though there isn't much in the way of a social life for her so group activities suited to her abilities might be helpful: a walking group, perhaps. Or, if she is not very mobile, is ther something else she might enjoy? Somewhere she can meet other people, maybe make new friends, or at the very least, interact.



