Author::::1789wasAgoodYear
DateTime::::2016-03-11T12:17:41Z
I feel for you. My ex partner (who was still my best friend) was an alcoholic. When I could see it was controlling him and he had no control I tried to help. Looked up loads of information about how to broach the subject and did many years of "your memory was better before you started drinking" and "you didn't catch so many colds before you started drinking" and "<insert concern element> before you started drinking". I did all the things that they suggested to no avail. He always had a reasonable excuse for the drinking which I knew was to validate his actions not to relieve my concerns. At one point I even lost patience after he had been very nasty and told him point blank he was an alcoholic. By the time this happened he was in full paranoid mode and thought everyone was out to get him. I got no where and he died because he was an alcoholic.



